energy usage cybersecurity telecommunications and reporting obligations in  the company was the first investment for silicon valley venture capital firm andreessen horowitz the company has approximately  customers including small companies as well as corporations such as bank of america metlife cisco microsoft starbucks jpmorgan chase goldman sachs boeing target xerox cocacola and directv contents  history  technology business management council  awards and recognition  references  external links historyedit the company was founded in  by sunny gupta kurt shintaffer and paul mclachlan prior to founding the company gupta and shintaffer worked together at iconclude before it was purchased by opsware in  in november  the company received  million in funding from madrona venture group and greylock partners while it was operating in stealth mode apptio raised an additional  million dollars in series b funding from the newly formed andersson horrowitz fund in  in  the company raised an additional  million in series c funding led by shasta ventures with participation from previous investors in march  the company raised an additional  million in series d funding to continue scaling hiring and expanding its services in  apptio raised an additional  million in series e funding bringing its total raised to  million from firms including greylock partners madrona venture group janus capital and t rowe price in march  apptio opened offices in sydney and melbourne australia in  the company announced that it was adding an office in denver apptio added another international office in march  when it announced it would open an office in paris france on september   apptio raised  million with its ipo technology business management counciledit apptio founded the technology business management council in  a nonprofit organization that had over  cios and other senior it leaders by  it was reported by the puget sound business journal that the council “aims to help it departments run like businesses by setting standards and best practices”  the council held its first conference in november  awards and recognitionedit in  ceo gupta was among ernst  young’s entrepreneur of the year award winners the same year apptio received first place in seattle business magazine’s  best companies to work for large companies and received the magazine’s tech impact award for enterprise computing in  apptio was cited for innovation in enterprise technology by bank of america merrill lynch apptio cofounder and cto paul mclachlan received the puget sound business journal  innovator award the seattle times called apptio “the region’s next big tech company” in  in  the company was ranked  on the forbes cloud  list referencesedit  leadership apptio retrieved may     soper taylor february   apptio posts record revenue of m in its second quarter as public company geekwire retrieved may     a b apptio prices stock at  in ipo  retrieved    a b ovide shira  november  ipo candidate apptio adds  publiccompany veterans wsj digits retrieved  march    king rachel  may  tbm startup apptio raises m plans to expand global footprint zdnet retrieved  march    a b grant rebecca  may  andreessen horowitz’s first investment apptio closes m fifth round venturebeat retrieved  march    a b horton nick july   best companies to work for  large companies seattle business magazine retrieved  march    bond phillip j  nov  a new way to track government spending on technology the hill retrieved  jan    a b ricketts camille  august  first andreessen horowitz investment apptio raises m venture beat retrieved  march    apptio s registration statement website apptio august     a b hesseldahl arik  may  apptio lands  million series e from janus capital all things d retrieved  march    a b c dudley brier  november  apptio founder sunny gupta on building the region’s next big tech company the seattle times retrieved  march    kugiya hugo december   paul mclachlan winner  innovator award puget sound business j