ion dollars in series b funding from the newly formed andersson horrowitz fund in  in  the company raised an additional  million in series c funding led by shasta ventures with participation from previous investors in march  the company raised an additional  million in series d funding to continue scaling hiring and expanding its services in  apptio raised an additional  million in series e funding bringing its total raised to  million from firms including greylock partners madrona venture group janus capital and t rowe price in march  apptio opened offices in sydney and melbourne australia in  the company announced that it was adding an office in denver apptio added another international office in march  when it announced it would open an office in paris france on september   apptio raised  million with its ipo technology business management counciledit apptio founded the technology business management council in  a nonprofit organization that had over  cios and other senior it leaders by  it was reported by the puget sound business journal that the council “aims to help it departments run like businesses by setting standards and best practices”  the council held its first conference in november  awards and recognitionedit in  ceo gupta was among ernst  young’s entrepreneur of the year award winners the same year apptio received first place in seattle business magazine’s  best companies to work for large companies and received the magazine’s tech impact award for enterprise computing in  apptio was cited for innovation in enterprise technology by bank of america merrill lynch apptio cofounder and cto paul mclachlan received the puget sound business journal  innovator award the seattle times called apptio “the region’s next big tech company” in  in  the company was ranked  on the forbes cloud  list referencesedit  leadership apptio retrieved may     soper taylor february   apptio posts record revenue of m in its second quarter as public company geekwire retrieved ma